<!-- ── CUSTOMER LOGOS + TESTIMONIAL REMOVED 2026-05-03 ──
     Per CTO direction: prior content (Savills/CBRE/JLL/Knight Frank/Cushman
     & Wakefield trust strip + James Hartley / Meridian Property Group
     testimonial) was fabricated. Removed to comply with UK Consumer Protection
     from Unfair Trading Regulations 2008 (CPRs) reg 5 ("misleading actions")
     and the Digital Markets, Competition & Consumers Act 2024 prohibition on
     fake reviews. Re-introduce ONLY with verifiable, opt-in attestations
     from real customers (signed permission + reviewable case study). -->

<!-- ── ENTERPRISE-FRAMEWORKS visual-fix 10-05 (U-27a) ──
     Premium 6-card framework grid replacing the prior flat 5-logo strip. -->
<!-- VIS.B5 2026-05-20 — Framework grid REBUILT as a Stripe-style monochrome
     wordmark strip with hairline dividers. The legacy .framework-card grid
     was inheriting the Deterministic Engine's flex-grow which stretched each
     card child to fill 695px of card height — entire top 70% of each card
     read as empty. The strip pattern collapses the redundant card chrome:
     name + citation + 1-line outcome + arrow link, all in a horizontal row.
     Density without colour — exactly the credibility device the research
     digest recommended for pre-launch B2B SaaS without customer logos. -->
<!-- ── JTBD 3-PATH ARCHITECTURE 2026-05-21 (manifest Stage 1) ─────────────
     Per Principal Architect mandate: replace the flat product list with a
     Jobs-To-Be-Done architecture. Three paths funnel users to the right
     product cluster by INTENT, not by product name.
       Path A: Protect (risk mitigation — cyber + MEES)
       Path B: Comply (regulatory duty — CSRD + ESG)
       Path C: Win   (competitive advantage — PPN 002 + CrowMark) -->
<section class="hp-jtbd sv-section sv-section--primary reveal sf17-reveal" id="jtbd" aria-labelledby="hp-jtbd-heading">
  <div class="sv-container sv-container--wide sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-8">
    <div class="sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-3">
      <span class="sv-eyebrow">Where it hurts &middot; What we fix</span>
      <h2 id="hp-jtbd-heading" class="sv-h2">Three jobs. One platform.</h2>
      <p class="sv-text-secondary hp-jtbd-sub">Pick the job that's burning. CrowAgent's six products map to three jobs UK organisations actually do under statute.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sv-grid sv-grid--md hp-jtbd-grid">
      <article class="hp-jtbd-card" data-path="protect">
        <div class="hp-jtbd-card__inner">
          <span class="hp-jtbd-card__path-label">Path A</span>
          <h3 class="hp-jtbd-card__title">Protect</h3>
          <p class="hp-jtbd-card__lede">Avoid statutory fines &amp; security breach exposure.</p>
          <ul class="hp-jtbd-card__products" role="list">
            <li><a href="/crowcyber">CrowCyber &middot; Cyber Essentials v3.3 <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; NCSC</span></a></li>
            <li><a href="/crowagent-core">CrowAgent Core &middot; MEES Band C 2028 <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; SI 2015/962 reg 38</span></a></li>
          </ul>
          <a class="sv-btn sv-btn--ghost sv-btn--sm hp-jtbd-card__cta" href="/crowcyber" aria-label="Explore the Protect path — Cyber Essentials and MEES coverage">Start with Protect &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="hp-jtbd-card" data-path="comply">
        <div class="hp-jtbd-card__inner">
          <span class="hp-jtbd-card__path-label">Path B</span>
          <h3 class="hp-jtbd-card__title">Comply</h3>
          <p class="hp-jtbd-card__lede">Meet regulatory disclosure duty without the consultancy bill.</p>
          <ul class="hp-jtbd-card__products" role="list">
            <li><a href="/csrd">CSRD Checker &middot; Omnibus I scope <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; Directive (EU) 2026/470</span></a></li>
            <li><a href="/crowesg">CrowESG &middot; EFRAG VSME 2024 <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; Module B/C</span></a></li>
          </ul>
          <a class="sv-btn sv-btn--ghost sv-btn--sm hp-jtbd-card__cta" href="/csrd" aria-label="Explore the Comply path — CSRD and ESG reporting">Start with Comply &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="hp-jtbd-card" data-path="win">
        <div class="hp-jtbd-card__inner">
          <span class="hp-jtbd-card__path-label">Path C</span>
          <h3 class="hp-jtbd-card__title">Win</h3>
          <p class="hp-jtbd-card__lede">Score the public-sector bid; recover the late invoice with interest.</p>
          <ul class="hp-jtbd-card__products" role="list">
            <li><a href="/crowmark">CrowMark &middot; PPN 002 social value <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; Cabinet Office 10%</span></a></li>
            <li><a href="/crowcash">CrowCash &middot; Late Payment Act 1998 <span class="sv-text-tertiary">&middot; BoE base + 8%</span></a></li>
          </ul>
          <a class="sv-btn sv-btn--ghost sv-btn--sm hp-jtbd-card__cta" href="/crowmark" aria-label="Explore the Win path — PPN 002 and Late Payment">Start with Win &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── STATUTORY MOAT 2026-05-21 (manifest Stage 1) ───────────────────────
     High-density "statute-to-source" terminal card. Replaces fake-customer
     testimonials with verifiable regulatory citations — Apple/Stripe-grade
     trust device for pre-launch B2B SaaS. Each line traces a quantified
     exposure to its statutory source. -->
<section class="hp-moat sv-section sv-section--secondary reveal sf17-reveal" aria-labelledby="hp-moat-heading">
  <div class="sv-container sv-container--standard sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-6">
    <div class="sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-3">
      <span class="sv-eyebrow">The Statutory Moat</span>
      <h2 id="hp-moat-heading" class="sv-h2">Every number traces back to its statute.</h2>
      <p class="sv-text-secondary hp-moat-sub">CrowAgent does not generate compliance opinions. The engine cites the law.</p>
    </div>
    <pre class="hp-moat-terminal" aria-label="Statute-to-source citations"><code><span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// MEES: trace every £150,000 penalty to its statute</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">SI 2015/962 reg 38</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">£150,000 max</span> per non-domestic property, rateable-value formula

<span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// PPN 002: trace every social-value bid floor to its policy</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">Cabinet Office PPN 002</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">10% minimum weighting</span> on all in-scope public-sector tenders

<span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// Late Payment: trace every interest claim to its Act</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">Late Payment Act 1998 &middot; SI 2002/1674</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">BoE base&nbsp;+&nbsp;8%</span> + £40 / £70 / £100 statutory compensation

<span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// Cyber Essentials: trace every control to NCSC's published spec</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">NCSC Cyber Essentials v3.3 (Danzell)</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">44 + 22 controls</span>, in force 27 Apr 2026

<span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// CSRD Omnibus I: trace every threshold to the Directive</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">Directive (EU) 2026/470</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">&gt;1,000 employees AND &gt;&euro;450M turnover</span>

<span class="hp-moat-prompt">crowagent&nbsp;&rsaquo;</span> <span class="hp-moat-comment">// EFRAG VSME: trace every voluntary disclosure to its standard</span>
<span class="hp-moat-source">EFRAG VSME 2024</span><span class="hp-moat-sep"> &rsaquo; </span><span class="hp-moat-amount">Module B + Module C</span> (Basic + Comprehensive)</code></pre>
    <p class="hp-moat-fineprint sv-text-tertiary">UK CPRs 2008 reg 5: every claim above traces to a public regulatory source. No customer testimonials. No fabricated metrics.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="hp-frameworks-strip sv-section sv-section--secondary reveal sf17-reveal" id="compliance-frameworks" aria-labelledby="hp-frameworks-heading">
  <div class="sv-container sv-container--wide sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-8">
    <div class="sv-stack sv-stack--align-center sv-stack--gap-3">
      <span class="sv-eyebrow">Built on UK + EU regulation</span>
