<!-- visual-fix 2026-05-10 (E-HOME 10-10): root-cause repeat of the
     2026-05-09 incident. The earlier comment claimed `.reveal` had been
     removed, but it had been re-added (likely by a downstream merge).
     IntersectionObserver was leaving this section at opacity:0 across
     desktop/tablet/mobile (verified 2026-05-10 with computed-style
     diagnostic at desktop=0, tablet=0, mobile=0). Removing `.reveal`
     keeps the section permanently visible; CSS belt-and-braces in the
     E-HOME 10-10 styles.css block guards against future regressions. -->
<!-- ENH 7 (modified) — pre-customer methodology statements.
     Customer testimonials cannot ship pre-customer per UK CPRs 2008 reg 5
     and the CTO directive at index.html:410. We replace ENH 7's "testimonial
     cards" with explicitly-labelled methodology statements that cite the
     statute backing each engine. Will be replaced with real customer
     attestations once early users sign off (Q3 2026). -->
<section class="sf18-method-stmts section-tone-0 sf17-reveal" aria-label="Engine methodology statements">
  <div class="wrap container-standard">
    <div class="sh force-center">
      <div class="sh-label">Methodology</div>
      <h2>Every engine cites the regulation that drives it.</h2>
      <p class="steps-sub">No marketing claims, no opinion. Every penalty, score, interest figure and threshold traces to the named statute.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sf18-method-grid">
      <article class="sf18-method-card">
        <div class="sf18-method-eyebrow ca-eyebrow">SI 2015/962 reg 38</div>
        <p class="sf18-method-body">MEES penalty exposure uses the rateable-value formula in regulation 38, capped at £150,000 per property. Short and long breach tiers per statute, not flat estimates.</p>
        <div class="sf18-method-engine">CrowAgent Core <span class="sf18-method-engine-sep">·</span> MEES engine</div>
      </article>
      <article class="sf18-method-card">
        <div class="sf18-method-eyebrow ca-eyebrow">PPN 002 + Oxford SVB</div>
        <p class="sf18-method-body">Social-value scoring follows PPN 002 (Cabinet Office, 2025) with proxy values from the Oxford Social Value Bank 2023-24 edition. The library Crown Commercial Service buyers score against.</p>
        <div class="sf18-method-engine">CrowMark <span class="sf18-method-engine-sep">·</span> PPN 002 engine</div>
      </article>
      <article class="sf18-method-card">
        <div class="sf18-method-eyebrow ca-eyebrow">SI 2002/1674 + Late Payment Act 1998</div>
        <p class="sf18-method-body">Statutory interest at Bank of England base + 8% plus £40 / £70 / £100 fixed compensation per overdue invoice, calculated to the penny.</p>
        <div class="sf18-method-engine">CrowCash <span class="sf18-method-engine-sep">·</span> Late Payment engine</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

