<!-- ENH 15 — API showcase. Tagged "Preview" so the endpoint isn't presented
     as GA — the API surface is a documented capability but pre-customer
     access is by request only (UK CPRs reg 5 honest framing). -->
<section class="sf18-api-section section-tone-1 sf17-reveal" aria-label="CrowAgent API preview">
  <div class="wrap container-standard sf18-api-grid">
    <div class="sf18-api-copy">
      <div class="sh-label">Developer surface <span class="sf18-preview-tag">Preview</span></div>
      <h2>Every compliance engine, available via API.</h2>
      <p class="u-body-muted">Embed MEES penalty calculation, PPN 002 social-value scoring, Cyber Essentials evidence checks and CSRD scope tests in your own systems. Statute-cited responses, JSON, REST. Early access by request, public docs land Q3 2026.</p>
      <div class="sf18-api-stats" role="list">
        <span class="sf18-api-stat" role="listitem"><strong>99.5%</strong><span>uptime target</span></span>
        <span class="sf18-api-stat" role="listitem"><strong>REST</strong><span>JSON · OAuth 2.0</span></span>
        <span class="sf18-api-stat" role="listitem"><strong>UK</strong><span>data residency</span></span>
      </div>
      <a class="sv-btn sv-btn--md sv-btn--ghost" href="/contact">Request developer access &rarr;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="sf18-code-block" aria-label="MEES penalty calculation API example">
      <div class="sf18-code-header">
        <span class="sf18-traffic" aria-hidden="true"><span class="r"></span><span class="y"></span><span class="g"></span></span>
        <span class="sf18-code-filename">mees-check.js · illustrative</span>
      </div>
<pre class="sf18-code-pre" id="sf18-api-snippet"><span class="sf18-code-comment">// CrowAgent API, MEES penalty calculation (preview shape)</span>
<span class="sf18-code-keyword">const</span> response = <span class="sf18-code-keyword">await</span> <span class="sf18-code-function">fetch</span>(<span class="sf18-code-string">'https://api.crowagent.ai/v1/mees'</span>, {
  method: <span class="sf18-code-string">'POST'</span>,
  headers: {
    <span class="sf18-code-string">'Authorization'</span>: <span class="sf18-code-string">'Bearer ca_preview_••••••••••••'</span>,
    <span class="sf18-code-string">'Content-Type'</span>: <span class="sf18-code-string">'application/json'</span>,
  },
  body: <span class="sf18-code-function">JSON</span>.<span class="sf18-code-function">stringify</span>({
    postcode: <span class="sf18-code-string">'EC1A 1BB'</span>,
    rateable_value: <span class="sf18-code-number">85000</span>,
    current_band: <span class="sf18-code-string">'D'</span>,
    breach_duration: <span class="sf18-code-string">'long'</span>,
  }),
});
<span class="sf18-code-comment">// Returns statute-cited penalty per SI 2015/962 reg 38.</span></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── METHODOLOGY TRANSPARENCY ── -->
<section class="reveal sf17-reveal section-padding section-tone-0" aria-label="Our methodology">
  <div class="wrap container-standard">
    <div class="sh">
      <div class="sh-label">Our methodology</div>
      <h2>Every output traces back to its source</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="u-body-muted u-section-intro u-text-center">
      CrowAgent does not generate compliance opinions. The platform applies published rules, thresholds, and methodologies from the regulatory sources your team already works with.
    </p>
    <!-- SF10 2026-05-17: methodology grid now uses 4 / 2+2 / 1+1+1+1 responsive
         layout (never 3+1 orphan) via .sf10-methodology-grid in styles.css §7. -->
    <div class="sf10-methodology-grid">
      <div class="sv-card accent-teal card">
        <div class="u-source-label">SI 2015/962 reg 38</div>
        <div class="u-stat-title">MEES penalty calculation</div>
        <p>Penalty exposure uses the rateable-value formula in SI 2015/962 reg 38. Short breach (less than three months) is capped at 10 percent of rateable value, with statutory tier caps. Long breach (three months or more) is capped at 20 percent of rateable value, up to a £150,000 maximum per property.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-card accent-lime card">
        <div class="u-source-label">PPN 002 + Oxford SVB 2023-24</div>
        <div class="u-stat-title">Social value scoring</div>
        <p>Mission mapping follows the PPN 002 social value model. Proxy values come from the Oxford Social Value Bank 2023-24 edition, stored in our database and updated when new editions are published.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-card accent-sky card">
        <div class="u-source-label">HM Treasury Green Book 2022</div>
        <div class="u-stat-title">NPV financial modelling</div>
        <!-- REVIEW: "2% energy escalation rate from Ofgem SME data" — cite specific Ofgem data series -->
        <p>All retrofit cost comparisons use a 3.5% discount rate from HM Treasury Green Book methodology, the standard for UK public sector investment appraisal, with a 2% energy escalation rate from Ofgem SME data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-card accent-mark card">
        <div class="u-source-label">Directive (EU) 2026/470</div>
        <div class="u-stat-title">CSRD Omnibus I thresholds</div>
        <p>The CSRD checker applies the post-Omnibus I thresholds: more than 1,000 employees AND more than &euro;450M turnover. Both conditions must be met. Previous thresholds (250 employees / &euro;40M) are superseded.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

